PlanGrid founders Tracy Young, Kenny Stone, Ryan Sutton-Gee and Ralph Gootee

metatags.twitter:title: Sequoia Capital - Check out highlights from Doug Leone and PlanGrid...
metatags.og:title: Sequoia Capital - Check out highlights from Doug Leone and PlanGrid founder Tracy Young's #StanfordETL discussion: Doug: If you want to build a company, don’t intellectualize stuff you know nothing about. Solve your own problem like Airbnb and PlanGrid have. Tracy: As a startup, there are always problems coming your way. You have to make sure you’re solving the right problems. Doug: We help companies recruit world-class engineers early on. If you miss on your first two engineers, it’s very hard to recover. Tracy: We want to show the world how to build a company that takes care of its employees and provides undeniable value to its customers.  Doug: Write your values in pen, and your strategies and tactics in pencil. Tracy: Surround yourself with people you can learn from. Believe in yourself and dive into areas you don’t know. Grow.
